Currently we use whether a grouping is in-axis or not to determine if it should make it into `_selected_obj`. This is almost the same as using `exclusions`
column3: the grouping data may arise from a column and hence should be excluded
column4: however the grouping data is not the column itself but rather derived from the column
column5: so it is not technically in-axis. Such columns should not make it into `_selected_obj`
column6: so we should prefer using excluded directly rather than in-axis.
